commit_message:
Add changes to conntrackd logging

* Reduce time of storing conntrackd-stats logs
  to 1 day
* Enable conntrackd log with storing for 7 days

Change-Id: I5afc09a14c17eba4fa96ffb8f89228340c96bf67
Closes-Bug: 1466006

commit_message:
Fix quota-update stuck in deleting when nova-compute startup finish

Quotas are not updated correctly for the instances whose task_state is
in deleting status during the nova-compute init_host call.

Added code to pass correct quota to the _delete_instance method.

(cherry picked from commit 71e99b1d56627e8a929f21b88e672f8ee34a53a1)

Change-Id: Ida84d2d49d46540e0581dc3a58844c30bc1d2cff
Partial-Bug: 1296414

commit_message:
Remove DefaultSignalTransport from top-level template

This hasn't been properly wired in for a while AFAICT, so it makes
sense to remove it, and introduce a value via parameter_defaults
which enables easier global selection of a particular transport
without passing the value down through all the nested stacks.

Change-Id: Icd830aea00768e65adc1df1287440fdab98058f9

commit_message:
Remove NO_SIGNAL from Controller|ObjectSwiftDeployment

We want to know this deployment succeeded, again the
ControllerAllNodesPostDeployment depends_on this, which implies
it should actually be done before doing the PostDeployment stuff,
which is impossible to determine with NO_SIGNAL.

Change-Id: I46d23bce8762ac414e4de82cf42193694aebb763

commit_message:
Remove NO_SIGNAL from ControllerBootstrapNodeDeployment

We need to be sure the boostrap node data has been propagated to the
cluster before proceeding with configuration, because
ControllerNodesPostDeployment consumes the data put in place by this
and depends_on for serialization, which is essentially meaningless when
combined with NO_SIGNAL.

Change-Id: I73a1e5a2cda4c79f457bfbd9ce2836dc5c1902cc

commit_message:
We should whitelist bash rather than sh

Otherwise the annoying message:

WARNING:test command found but not installed in testenv
  cmd: /bin/bash
Maybe forgot to specify a dependency?

is not going away

Closes-bug: #1466330

Change-Id: I0681b4413eb2ed002aeaaa68cd3fc2beb5ed72c9

commit_message:
Add a new configuration option to configure LVM type

This patch proposes to add a new configuration option "CINDER_LVM_TYPE"
to decide which LVM type the LVM driver is going to use. It can be
either default or thin.

Change-Id: I209a832580919148ba58086e66601dc1a625f31c
Closes-Bug: #1466329

commit_message:
[install-guide-rst] Set up conditionals for distros

Add support for conditionals for the Install Guide.

This uses the tags:
* rdo
* obs
* ubuntu

Note that this is changed from the spec since sphinx does not accept a
"-". Also, I changed from opensuse to suse for brevity.

Adds new tox target so that "tox -e install-guides" builds only the
RST Install Guide.

implements bp installguide-liberty

Change-Id: Ibdfbc7ff294e56f52cd6f4ef59ceeb7b6af3e28a

commit_message:
Add a new parameter connector to migrate_volume_completion

Since the volume and the iscsi target need to remain the same as
the source volume after the migration, the connector is used to
reconnect to the volume after migration.

Change-Id: Id011649ef2c1d6af3a04ff9bf7835579712bb6fd
Partially-closes-bug: #1450649

commit_message:
Pass block device info in pre_live_migration

In case of block migration, this adds block device information to the
disk information handled by pre_live_migration, so that at least in the
case of libvirt no spurious files are created corresponding to volumes.

(cherry picked from commit 8489e4a2d100fa34f49a044f1973a163a4bfb8e5)

Co-Authored-By: florent.flament@cloudwatt.com
Change-Id: I373001e0ef0e4fe4ab900d399756f27101cfe5c8
Closes-Bug: 1376586

revisions:
[{'created': '2015-05-27 10:43:03.000000000', 'message': 'MOS-RN6.1 Neutron known and resolved issues

Adds Neutron known and resolved issues to the MOS 6.1 Release Notes
page:

- Pacemaker turns DHCP agent resource into unmanaged state
- same router namespace on two controllers;
- Instances receive DHCP NAKs during booting on
  clusters with Neutron networking;
- Critical error: neutron [-] AssertionError: Trying
  to re-send() an already-triggered event;
- HA neutron environment - there is no connectivity to the instance.

Change-Id: Ibca18a683371ec9161e5c7eedd24b235b3dd651c

commit_message:
MOS-RN6.1 Neutron known and resolved issues

Adds Neutron known and resolved issues to the MOS 6.1 Release Notes
page:

- Pacemaker turns DHCP agent resource into unmanaged state
- same router namespace on two controllers;
- Instances receive DHCP NAKs during booting on
  clusters with Neutron networking;
- HA neutron environment - there is no connectivity to the instance.

Change-Id: Ibca18a683371ec9161e5c7eedd24b235b3dd651c

commit_message:
Change the way error are returned from API to JSON

Previously we used just strings. It's not a breaking change in terms
of API, but it will lead to less readable errors for older clients.

Nice side effect of this change is that exceptions are no longer
reported as HTML.

In-tree client was updated, as separate one is not set up yet.

Change-Id: Ice3111e08f8716d904efc4869c6d2ded25e23e2e
Closes-Bug: #1465347

commit_message:
WIP: Add support for dynamic config files

Ansible will read a standard openstack ini-style config and then
convert it to a json string representation of that file. Ansible can
use that string to generate a named variable that can be parsed back to
its original form with env_parser.py

env_parser.py can run beside crudini for backward compatibility

Partially Implements Blueprint: dynamic-configuration

Change-Id: If5bb7ddcd2b66224a864ddcaaeccbcfa5f037d9d

commit_message:
Cluster and node design doc

This is a initial version of the developer document. It describes the
targeted use cases and the design decisions made to meet the requirements.
This patch only contains docs related to cluster and node. Following
patch will provide doc on other objects and/or components.

Change-Id: I9b435ee0e890cb4e985ce739cf8948b7bbb93d95

Put output of docs job into doc/build/html

This is the path where jenkins/scripts/run-docs.sh that is used by gate
to generate project documentation expects to see the output.

commit_message:
Add devices to update in RPC call security_groups_provider_updated

When a security_groups_provider_updated is received then a global
refresh of the firewall is performed. This can be avoided if the
plugins pass as parameter of the call the devices that belongs to
the network updated.

Partially-Implements: blueprint restructure-l2-agent
Change-Id: I1e78f3a5ec7e5c5bcba338a0097566422411ef7e

commit_message:
Explicit error for wrong resource metadata format

When creating sample with wrong resource metadata format, Ceilometer CLI
will return a ValueError about json decoding, this change provide a more
explicit error info.

Change-Id: I18e757ddb319fbf0ffad13c07528355785ea5e9a
Closes-Bug: 1465193

commit_message:
Remove hv_type translation shim for powervm

Commit d05567cc3fcb8849402f7036895ea5f40f7e1a1f added a temporary
translation shim so that the 'powervm' hypervisor type name in older
images used by the powervc driver in stackforge would not fail to
schedule due to an invalid (unregistered) hypervisor type.

The agreement from the powervc driver maintainers in stackforge was that
they'd put an image metadata translation shim in their driver so this
could be removed from nova in Liberty, which is now.

UpgradeImpact: Users of the nova-powervc driver from stackforge will
               need to move to a version of that driver which
               translates 'powervm' image metadata properly for
               scheduling, or update the image metadata manually.

Change-Id: I31be654c817a00df2b4b51c184600c0c51c86443

network_associate.

commit_message:
Get rid of oslo-incubator copy of middleware

We have already moved away from openstack/common/middleware modules
to the oslo_middlware library. Let us cleanup the remaining files
here.

Change-Id: I701b08a28884eb56d12f2829483fe94aa8d2fd1d

supported distro.

commit_message:
Remove unnecessary has_client() checks

After moving some resources into main tree, and also
according some clients are required in heat registation,
we should remove some unnecessary has_client() checks.
And this change will remove the unnecessary
available_resource_mapping() defination.

Change-Id: Ia88826ca9698886f05e55ed68ef773bfe3c8c696

Many of these auth tests will fail on a slower system or when
using the debugger. If the test takes too long it fails when
token timestamps are compared.

The strategy to fix this is to take control of the clock and not

Closes-Bug: 1464366
'}]
commit_message:
Fix tests failing on slower system

Many of these auth tests will fail on a slower system or when
using the debugger. If the test takes too long it fails when
token timestamps are compared.

The strategy to fix this is to take control of the clock and not
depend on the external environment.

Change-Id: Ib00ba4aebfe4886c3d93e77f7b216139bdf2acf8
Closes-Bug: 1464366

commit_message:
VMware: detach cinder volume when instance destroyed

Ensure that the cinder volume is detached when the instance is destroyed.
When an instance has an attached cinder volume we need to ensure that
the volume is detached prior to deleting the VM on the backend.

Closes-bug: #1439168

Change-Id: I95dfbec3036270c07c7edbda35574fee5f029ddb

Update the quickstart guide to explain how to use bay-update
to update the node_count attribute of a bay.

Closes-Bug: 1464936

commit_message:
Update version for Liberty

Update the version for Liberty, switching from date-based versioning
to pre-versioning using SemVer. See
http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2015-May/065211.html
and
http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2015-June/067082.html
for details.

Change-Id: I6a35fa0dda798fad93b804d00a46af80f08d475c

I did this as we agreed on IRC and John Garbutt recommended this.
Cited from https://blueprints.launchpad.net/nova/+spec/rename-pcs-to-virtuozzo:

We are not happy about the end user impact here, this will need a very short spec to agree the upgrade impact here. If we cover that in the above description quickly, maybe we avoid creating a spec, but I think spec is the quickest way to get this approved. --johnthetubaguy 11th June 2015'}, {'account_id': 12408, 'date': '2015-06-15 14:41:31.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

(1 comment)'}, {'account_id': 1849, 'date': '2015-06-16 08:05:44.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1

looks good to me, I have a minor concern about the deprecation period of one release based on the availability of the right version of libvirt though. Why not extend the deprecation cycle for a few releases?'}, {'account_id': 12408, 'date': '2015-06-16 08:09:50.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

Actually I don't mind. I just chose the period to minimal possible according to deprecation policy."}, {'account_id': 1779, 'date': '2015-06-16 09:19:13.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+2

I'm not too fussed about the length of deprecation cycle. Parallels was new in Kilo, so I think there will be relatively few users impacted by the rename, so 1 cycle will likely be long enough for them to change. The level of development in the libvirt parallels^H^H^H^Hvirtuosso driver is still quite high, so users are pretty likely to update their libvirt to get access to the improved impl anyway"}, {'account_id': 12408, 'date': '2015-06-16 13:29:36.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 2.'}, {'account_id': 12408, 'date': '2015-06-16 13:32:12.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

commit_message:
libvirt: rename 'parallels' virt_type to 'vz'

This change proposes to rename 'parallels' virt_type to 'vz'
as soon as Parallels Cloud Server was renamed to Virtuozzo.

Implements blueprint rename-pcs-to-virtuozzo

Change-Id: I865479a3472b63e1003221fb3e14fcb3d86ffaa1

commit_message:
Made a several-seconds checking&waiting for object to be deleted

There is a bug https://bugs.launchpad.net/tempest/+bug/1452915
that describes failing test_get_object_after_expiry_time test
because in real clouds hardcoded 3 seconds waiting for the
container is not enough. Replaced hardcoded 3 seconds with the
checking and waiting in a loop for object to be deleted.

Change-Id: If90d9ef047344e2e094aa1b143c93c9fa4b56fbd
Closes-Bug: #1452915

commit_message:
Update 3PAR user config help strings

The 3PAR drivers no longer require a user to have the 'super'
access role. This patch simply updates the help strings for the
3PAR username and password to reflect that an 'edit' role will
be sufficient.

Change-Id: Iad5631ff93690e93c281e4c86ce78f79a40ee163
Closes-Bug: 1465428

commit_message:
Added tests for checking of handling AssertionErrors

The following tests have been added:
*test_engine_service.test_validate_new_stack_handle_assertion_error
*test_stack.test_validate_assertion_exception_rethrow
*test_stack_resource.test_validate_assertion_exception_rethrow

These tests are focused on checking the cases when we should
return 500 status codes and log the tracebacks for
AssertionException, but not wrap in the validation exception.

Related commit: I71d91a5413d7f026b332014487583b7f2762b322
Closes-Bug: #1456839
Change-Id: I30c2a91043465aa14c39cae5fb0b0d2c17e059e9

commit_message:
Reusable empty template

Refactored the empty template and added it to template module so that it
can be re-used else where. In convergence it is needed for rolling back
when create fails. Also needed for deleting stack, that is, update the
stack with empty template.

The empty_template method can be passed a template header (version) in
order to get an empty template of that version, otherwise by default, an
empty HOT template is returned.

commit_message:
Merge quota_sets functional tests of v2 and v2.1

Currently v2 and v2.1 have separate functional tests and their
corresponding sample files. As v2 and v2.1 are supposed to be identical,
there is overhead to maintain two set of functional tests and sample files.
We can have one set of tests which can run for both v2 and v2.1.

This commit merges quota_sets functional tests.

In V2 quota has following extensions
- os-server-group-quotas
- os-quota-sets
- os-extended-quotas
- os-user-quotas

In V2.1, all the extensions from V2 are merged into os-quota-sets.

Change-Id: Ic54a5745608cec3fe7a5b035f232f3a04d2d1e77

commit_message:
Actually install the requirements repo.

The requirements repo has had a setup.cfg etc for a long time but only
recently started using it. As it now has dependencies, we need to pip
install it. To preserve compat with older requirements repos I haven't
changed the call to invoke update-requirements yet, as we still have
the update.py symlink.

The pbr install is moved before requirements to ensure we don't
trigger easy-install.

Change-Id: I7d7e91694c9145fac0ddab8a9de5f789d723c641

commit_message:
Improving the code coverage for ACL related changes

In recent ACL code changes, there were couple of lines which did not
have coverage so adding tests to cover those. Also identified one
minor issue in corner case so fixing it.

Brought back acls controller coverage to 100%

After ACL change, there was another change in Containers controller
where container id is verified and set in its pecan _lookup call.
If error, then returns not found error from there only. So now id
check is not needed in Container ACLs logic. So removing that code.

Change-Id: Ib1dcb7ec74d237d305e81b93e7df467cd4bf3744

At present, redstack clones the most recent version of devstack. Sometimes this
is undesirable as devstack can at times become unstable. A solution to this
would be to add an environment variable or option to redstack to specify the
branch of devstack to use (with the default remaining 'master').

With this change you can now specify:

DEVSTACK_BRANCH=stable/kilo ./redstack install

and redstack would switch to the stable/kilo branch before running './stack.sh'
Optionally, for persistence, it can be defined in either options.rc or

Change-Id: I50c64db917bb87bac5d1b1d4d0231270577e26a8
Closes-Bug: #1449627
"}, {'created': '2015-06-03 21:08:19.000000000', 'message': "Allow specifying project branch in redstack

At present, redstack clones the most recent version of devstack and
each project.  Sometimes this is undesirable as these repositories can
become unstable.  A solution to this would be to add an environment
variable or option to redstack to specify the branch or commit to use
(with the default remaining 'master').

With this change you can now specify scenarios like:

- To switch all projects (including devstack) to a stable branch:
PROJECT_BRANCH=stable/kilo ./redstack install

- To switch all projects to a stable branch, but have a specific
  devstack commit used:
PROJECT_BRANCH=stable/kilo DEVSTACK_BRANCH=7ef2464 ./redstack install

- To switch all projects (including devstack) to a stable branch,
but have a specific commit for Nova:
PROJECT_BRANCH=stable/kilo NOVA_BRANCH=7ef2464 ./redstack install

Redstack would then switch to the corresponding branch/commit before
running './stack.sh'

Optionally, for persistence, these variables can be defined in either
options.rc or ~/.redstack.options.rc

The repos are switched, even if the project directories already existed.

If an invalid branch/commit is specified, redstack stops with an error
message.

The following environment variables are now supported (in order of
precedence):
<PROJECT>_BRANCH - where <PROJECT> is either DEVSTACK or is defined
                   in *projects-list
                   i.e. NOVA_BRANCH, CINDER_BRANCH, DEVSTACK_BRANCH
PROJECT_BRANCH

Note: Setting PROJECT_BRANCH will *not* affect the Trove project - you
must use TROVE_BRANCH specifically for that.

Change-Id: I50c64db917bb87bac5d1b1d4d0231270577e26a8
Closes-Bug: #1449627

commit_message:
Allow specifying project branch in redstack

At present, redstack clones the most recent version of devstack and
each project.  Sometimes this is undesirable as these repositories can
become unstable.  A solution to this would be to add an environment
variable or option to redstack to specify the branch or commit to use
(with the default remaining 'master').

With this change you can now specify scenarios like:

- To switch all projects (including devstack) to a stable branch:
PROJECT_BRANCH=stable/kilo ./redstack install

- To switch all projects to a stable branch, but have a specific
  devstack commit used:
PROJECT_BRANCH=stable/kilo DEVSTACK_BRANCH=7ef2464 ./redstack install

- To switch all projects (including devstack) to a stable branch,
but have a specific commit for Nova:
PROJECT_BRANCH=stable/kilo NOVA_BRANCH=7ef2464 ./redstack install

- To switch all projects to a stable branch, but have a different
stable branch for the clients:
PROJECT_BRANCH=stable/juno PROJECT_CLIENT_BRANCH=stable/kilo ...

Redstack would then switch to the corresponding branches/commits
before running './stack.sh'

Optionally, for persistence, these variables can be defined in either
options.rc or ~/.redstack.options.rc

The repos are switched, even if the project directories already existed.

If an invalid branch/commit is specified, redstack stops with an error
message.

The following environment variables are now supported (in order of
precedence):
<PROJECT>_BRANCH - where <PROJECT> is either DEVSTACK or is defined
                   in *projects-list
                   i.e. NOVA_BRANCH, CINDER_BRANCH, DEVSTACK_BRANCH
PROJECT_CLIENT_BRANCH
PROJECT_BRANCH

Note: Setting PROJECT_BRANCH or PROJECT_CLIENT_BRANCH will *not*
affect the Trove project - you must use TROVE_BRANCH and
PYTHON_TROVECLIENT specifically for that.

Change-Id: I50c64db917bb87bac5d1b1d4d0231270577e26a8
Closes-Bug: #1449627

commit_message:
Initial changes for testing VM creation for CentOS

Adding updates to the VM creation steps to hopefully allow for
CentOS test VMs to be able to be fired up.  Also refactors basic
OS support for the module to be more flexible by loading defaults
from files.

Change-Id: Ie4456d199dd3d965e533070f4321f50075dfe1df

commit_message:
We should whitelist bash rather than sh

Otherwise the annoying message:

WARNING:test command found but not installed in testenv
  cmd: /bin/bash
Maybe forgot to specify a dependency?

is not going away

Change-Id: I017aa15e9f79e2c70417b7188ba23e731feac110

commit_message:
SQL scripts should not manage transactions

This bug was fixed a while back, but the migration added for
multi-attach reintroduced it for its sqlite_downgrade file.

This patch removes it.

blueprint enable-mysql-connector

Change-Id: Iaec8713bf5cf36bcc97afbca8dd025cda9c2238d
Closes-Bug: 1368391

commit_message:
Add note on openrc and zsh

Add a note about running openrc through bash for import into zsh, as
shown by Chmouel Boudjnah in I5b6c8cfedcdd36efb4cbc91831501ee5c9c3b1d1

Change-Id: I5f1c9fc3fdc045cf6fb69af13f6264a81bf5f763
Closes-Bug: #1460656

revisions:
[{'created': '2015-06-16 09:54:07.000000000', 'message': 'Fix incompatiblity issue in VNX manila driver

Where running Manila With VNX File OE 8.1.6 or later,
If user creates a NFS share via VNX Manila driver,
driver will report nas command issue when setting nfs permssion.
This fix will use updated nas command to resolve it.

Change-Id: I0550cdf01278fa4e9aeed7891152fed6dcc0eefc
Closes-Bug: #1465543
'}, {'created': '2015-06-16 09:58:22.000000000', 'message': 'Fix incompatiblity issue in VNX manila driver

When running Manila with VNX File OE 8.1.6 or later,
if user creates a NFS share in Manila, driver will
report nas command error when setting nfs permssion.

This fix will use updated nas command to resolve it.

Change-Id: I0550cdf01278fa4e9aeed7891152fed6dcc0eefc
Closes-Bug: #1465543
'}, {'created': '2015-06-17 02:25:28.000000000', 'message': 'Fix incompatiblity issue in VNX manila driver

When running Manila with VNX File OE 8.1.6 or later,
if user creates a NFS share in Manila, driver will
report nas command error when setting nfs permssion.

commit_message:
Fix incompatiblity issue in VNX manila driver

When running Manila with VNX File OE 8.1.6 or later,
if user creates a NFS share in Manila, driver will
report nas command error when setting nfs permssion.

This fix will use updated nas command to resolve it.

Change-Id: I0550cdf01278fa4e9aeed7891152fed6dcc0eefc
Closes-Bug: #1465543

commit_message:
Use python-six shim for assertRaisesRegex/p

Python2 uses assertRaisesRegexp while Python3 uses assertRaisesRegex.
Use the compatability shim in six for this:
https://pythonhosted.org/six/#unittest-assertions

Change-Id: I28ce94207567e0b3c28c634119757a1d68e955f2
Closes-Bug: #1462370

commit_message:
ovsdb: session.rpc never initialized

Previously, if idl.Transaction.commit_block() returned a status of
TRY_AGAIN we would check self.api.idl._session.rpc.status which would
result in an attribute error as rpc is None.

This patch fixes this attribute error by removing this unneeded check. In
addtion, the force_reconnect() is also removed as ovs.jsonrpc handles
reconnecting automatically for us.

Change-Id: Ibf3ce5cd3432845f8938a1d83637ecf59b14b5ca
Closes-bug: 1465889

commit_message:
compute: stop handling virt lifecycle events in cleanup_host()

When rebooting a compute host, guest VMs can be getting shutdown
automatically by the hypervisor and the virt driver is sending events to
the compute manager to handle them. If the compute service is still up
while this happens it will try to call the stop API to power off the
instance and update the database to show the instance as stopped.

When the compute service comes back up and events come in from the virt
driver that the guest VMs are running, nova will see that the vm_state
on the instance in the nova database is STOPPED and shut down the
instance by calling the stop API (basically ignoring what the virt
driver / hypervisor tells nova is the state of the guest VM).

Alternatively, if the compute service shuts down after changing the
intance task_state to 'powering-off' but before the stop API cast is
complete, the instance can be in a strange vm_state/task_state
combination that requires the admin to manually reset the task_state to
recover the instance.

Let's just try to avoid some of this mess by disconnecting the event
handling when the compute service is shutting down like we do for
neutron VIF plugging events. There could still be races here if the
compute service is shutting down after the hypervisor (e.g. libvirtd),
but this is at least a best attempt to do the mitigate the potential
damage.

Closes-Bug: #1444630
Related-Bug: #1293480
Related-Bug: #1408176

Conflicts:
	nova/compute/manager.py
	nova/tests/unit/compute/test_compute_mgr.py

Change-Id: I1a321371dff7933cdd11d31d9f9c2a2f850fd8d9
(cherry picked from commit d1fb8d0fbdd6cb95c43b02f754409f1c728e8cd0)

commit_message:
Update PUT methods to send update through queue

Update controller_simulator handler to behave clearly through operations
Update handler interface to utilize ids instead of full objects
Update controllers to utilize new handler parameters
Update tests to follow new controller behavior
Update queue producer and test to include data_models for updates

Change-Id: I3423ccf5b3e3c0810d000454df984fca4ec4dbbd

commit_message:
Remove install_venv_common and fix typo in memorycache

We don't really use install_venv_common anywhere, so let's
get rid of it. Also a typo crept into memorycache.py somehow
(probably bad copy of update.py/sh script during last sync).
Fixed that as well.

Change-Id: I6869a332a071eca74d731443baf921e2ae96572e

commit_message:
Explicitly add json schema validator for schema validation

JSON Schema use validator (draft3 or draft4) to validate the
given schema against given instance.
By default it use draft4 validator which is current one. If new validator
will be released in future and that become default then, there might be some
compatibility issues between draft4 and new version.

For example from draft3 to draft4, 'ip-version' format has been changed to 'ipv4'.

This commits explicitly pass the validator while doing the schema validation.
Also adds unit tests to check the current version of validator.

If any new validator will be available in future, then we can use that by doing
proper modification in schema files if needed.

Change-Id: Ie11e3ba60926f247a82670b7da37d7890d16280c

commit_message:
keystone_user password does not work

The openstack provider raises Puppet::Error::OpenstackUnauthorizedError
when the password is invalid.  In this case, just catch the error and
return nil to allow the password to be changed.

Change-Id: If87b5f1502d31ef5488305a923bf26937ea6b164
Closes-bug: 1465465

I think we should not add a vendor-specific flag but a feature flag like 'fip_need_router_with_gateway' (set to default because default Neutron implementation needs it)

I decided not to vote any +1/-1 to this change.

As a Neutron team, this kind of API behavior divergence is a serious problem and we need to define more strict API/scenario tests to avoid such kind of situation. I believe this is a fault of Neutron architecture.

On the other hand, it is what actually happens. Horizon team can accept this change.

Even though vendor-agnostic flag naming, we still need to take care of vendor-specific behaviors, so I don't have a positive feeling."}, {'account_id': 841, 'date': '2015-06-12 10:48:48.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 7:

I am still thinking this. The current implementation of Neutron L3 reference implementation has a limitation that ports on subnets directly connected to an external router can be associated to FIPs. Even when a port is reachable from an external router, if the port does not belong to a subnet directly connected to the external router, the port cannot be associated with a FIP. This is a limitation.

If a network backend has more intelligent network reachability check,
the current horizon logic can be a problem. This is a different case from the original bug report, but it can be fixed by the same change.

One question on Contrail behavior. In OpenContrail, can any IP address associated with a floating IP regardless of network topology?
Isn't a problem to list all ports on a tenant? (it is just from my curiosity.)"}, {'account_id': 841, 'date': '2015-06-12 10:55:04.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 7:

commit_message:
Allow to attach FIP without a router

The Default Neutron implementation needs a router with a gateway to associate a
FIP. So by default a topology check will be performed by horizon to list only
VM ports attached to a network which is itself attached to a router with an
external gateway. This is to prevent from setting a FIP to a port which will
fail with an error.

Some Neutron vendors do not require it. Some can even attach a FIP to any port
(e.g.: OpenContrail) owned by a tenant.

This patch adds a setting allowing to bypass the topology check in order to let
the user associate a FIP to an instance on a subnet with no router if the
Neutron backend allows it.

Change-Id: I1bf8bd0113a154c5e0bf0f75065b911f15db3e83
Closes-Bug: #1462902

commit_message:
Handle errors during glance image updates correctly

Before an UnboundLocalError would occur in case an error would happen
during image updates, because of incorrect referencing of a variable.
Moreover the error was muted by exceptions.handle with ignore=True,
and could result in an incorrect success message.
This change removes references to unused image variable and allows
exceptions to be handled by the function, that calls image_update.

Change-Id: I35ea98a146690565582dd9beea62941f97d32474
Closes-Bug: #1464991

commit_message:
Install iptables-services package for Ironic

devstack enables iptables service for ironic but it fails on
fedora. That is because related files are included in
iptables-services rpm and devstack doen't install it.

Change-Id: Ibe264427518bb9059bc54c6e945377fc354549a1
Closes-Bug: #1464483

[{'created': '2015-06-17 16:46:10.000000000', 'message': "Install python-libvirt for ceilometer only if n-cpu enabled

Nova is responsible for installing the libvirt package (if it is being
used). It is required by python-libvirt but python-libvirt only required
in ceilometer if nova compute is being used. There are some usage
scenarios where nova compute is not being used so in that case don't
install python-libvirt.

Change-Id: I0db66f1c0526e24ade98de85989a5ed8d37f0c4f
"}]
commit_message:
Install python-libvirt for ceilometer only if n-cpu enabled

Nova is responsible for installing the libvirt package (if it is being
used). It is required by python-libvirt but python-libvirt only required
in ceilometer if nova compute is being used. There are some usage
scenarios where nova compute is not being used so in that case don't
install python-libvirt.

Change-Id: I0db66f1c0526e24ade98de85989a5ed8d37f0c4f

commit_message:
Update version for Liberty

Update the version for Liberty, switching from date-based versioning
to pre-versioning using SemVer. See
http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2015-May/065211.html
and
http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2015-June/067082.html
for details.

Change-Id: I6a35fa0dda798fad93b804d00a46af80f08d475c

Update version for Liberty

Update the version for Liberty, switching from date-based versioning
to pre-versioning using SemVer. See
http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2015-May/065211.html
and
http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2015-June/067082.html
for details.

Change-Id: I6a35fa0dda798fad93b804d00a46af80f08d475c

commit_message:
Update version for Liberty

Update the version for Liberty, switching from date-based versioning
to pre-versioning using SemVer. See
http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2015-May/065211.html
and
http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2015-June/067082.html
for details.

Change-Id: I6a35fa0dda798fad93b804d00a46af80f08d475c

commit_message:
Add HGST Solutions connector

Adds a HGSTConnector class and hooks it up to use the HGST Solutions
protocol to attach/detach storage.  Uses the CLI to talk to the
Solutions data plane and assumes that the node in question is
already part of the domain.

Change-Id: I0a60c2e6b59d59f791cc1099a37fe4616ce58937
Implements: blueprint add-volume-driver-hgst-solutions

commit_message:
Added support for DellStorageCenter ISCSI cinder driver

The Dell Storage Center driver manages Storage Center arrays 
through Enterprise Manager. 

Added support to generate the cinder.conf for
the Dell Storage Center iscsi volume driver based on documentation here:
http://docs.openstack.org/kilo/config-reference/content/dell-storagecenter-driver.html

Change-Id: I397777f43dbbd7c86cfa2ca4392ff303030688f9

commit_message:
Update version for Liberty

Update the version for Liberty, switching from date-based versioning
to pre-versioning using SemVer. See
http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2015-May/065211.html
and
http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2015-June/067082.html
for details.

Change-Id: I6a35fa0dda798fad93b804d00a46af80f08d475c

commit_message:
Fix spelling of runlevel in init scripts

A number of the init templates in the OpenStack roles have the word
runlevel incorrectly spelt as runlelvl. This commit correct those
spelling mistakes.

Change-Id: I0d1b7d5c5cf088fecf07cf0e1bd676b4e4088e2b
Closes-bug: #1464603
(cherry picked from commit 8cbc495debec4cddc12690f10b2466e4db7550b9)

commit_message:
Move bandit requirement to test-requirements.txt

The update script for requirements doesn't update
test-requirements-bandit.txt automatically. Rather than update
that script, move the bandit requirement into
test-requirements.txt instead.

Change-Id: I331ffd378d80943b8884b4a62493096c54ad8948

commit_message:
Unit tests catch deprecated function usage

Rather than continue to call deprecated functions without knowing
it, have the unit tests fail when deprecated function is used.

Change-Id: I4e9893cb5bcd7382c968f876701720cb199af333

commit_message:
Common base class for unit tests

A common base class is defined to provide a place to put fixtures
that affect all tests. For example, we could add a fixture that
ensures that no deprecated function was used.

Change-Id: I93aa45fa8284d8cdd8b0f71f137a261610e31988

Core reviewers:

Please do _not_ use Workflow +1 on this specification.  I want to understand where the core reviewers stand on this specification and your voting helps me understand that.

Please vote +2 if you are satisfied the specification delivers our mission accepting there will be technical inaccuracies in the specification and your committed as a core reviewer to reviewing the work output of this specification.

Please abstain by leaving a note in the review log that you are abstaining from voting.

Please vote -1 if you are not satisfied the specification is consistent with our mission.  A -1 vote should not be placed for technical inaccuracies, questions, typos, or other trivial things.  A -1 vote indicates to me that I can't count on your help to execute this specification.

To veto the specification the -2 vote should be used.  Note I have no plan to handle a veto vote on this specification and suspect any veto votes would result in serious damage to our community.  You have been warned :)

A +1 vote is not a vote that is permittied by core reviewers in this case :)"}, {'account_id': 2834, 'date': '2015-06-17 15:33:05.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 6: Code-Review+2'}, {'account_id': 14119, 'date': '2015-06-17 16:28:52.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 6: Code-Review+2

Spec to Add Support for High Availability

Previously, a spec did not exist to define how Kolla will support
highly available OpenStack services.

Change-Id: I8fcc60f26d2cb98179be6b520c13abb22a372ecf

commit_message:
Added certificate support to KMIP secret store

The KMIP secret store can now store certificates. This change also
includes changes to the code to make it easier to support other secret
types besides keys.  This will include certificates, passphrases, and
opaque data.

Change-Id: Icf32dbd2048f710a09b58d02e4c31538da483351

commit_message:
Update 3PAR user config help strings

The 3PAR drivers no longer requires a user to have the 'super'
access role. This patch simply updates the help strings for the
3PAR username and password to reflect that an 'edit' role will
be sufficient.

DocImpact

Change-Id: I9b546953d06072dd614f92542b77e3a1a96f2eb5

commit_message:
Provide a means to get all installed plugins

Particular for use in writing error messages and help text it can be
useful to get a list of all the plugins that are installed on the
system. Provide a version that returns the classes as well so that you
don't have to reload the modules if the user is picking one.

Closes-Bug: #1423711
Change-Id: I021249eac8156c2d3ccbbacb7503184b6eb6e784
(cherry picked from commit f5e2aab08b9ce71067fade4af576062e5fdb7032)

commit_message:
Make normalize_endpoint_type public

This method is expected to be overridden from subclasses and should
therefore be public. It will also need to be called from keystoneclient.

Change-Id: Ic79ab9f3f5dd78bee1416aa4a1c8732548849949

Make _is_endpoint_type_match function public

abstract functions then we should at least have them public so
subclasses know what they are supposed to override.

commit_message:
Remove _get_service_endpoints function

This function was largely used because in keystoneclient we also had to
filter by an arbitrary attr/value filter combination. Now that we don't
have this requirement we don't really need the function and it is easier
to port this into keystoneclient if it doesn't exist.

Change-Id: I31d3b3445d1f8b9538363e8e323a6e97be7b1d6f

commit_message:
JSCS - Allow ignoring specific kinds of errors

"Line too long" messages will be common for long sentences passed
to gettext(). Also, sometimes long descriptions are helpful in
test describe() and it() descriptions.

For gettext(), we cannot break the line or the translation won't
work correctly. For test code, it is nice to not require developers
to workaround this JSCS limitation when writing test descriptions.

JSCS allows an error filter function. This patch creates a filter
that checks the specific line of a "line too long" error and
ignores it if it is a gettext, or a test file with it() or
describe() function.

Change-Id: I742c5fc1ef1a7235ee965be003a312d7a681fb62

The redis_vip should come from a Neutron Port as its cidr depends
on the Neutron Network configuration. This change adds 2 new files
and modifies 1 in the network/ports directory:

- noop.yaml - Passes through the ctlplane Controller IP (modified)
- ctlplane_vip.yaml - Creates a new VIP on the control plane
- vip.yaml - Creates a VIP on the named network (for isolated nets)

Also, changes to overcloud-without-mergepy.yaml create the
Redis Virtual IP. The standard resource registry was modified to
use noop.yaml for the new Redis VIP. The Puppet resource registry
was modified to use ctlplane_vip.yaml by default, but can be made
to use vip.yaml when network isolation is used by using an
environment file. vip.yaml will place the VIP according to the
ServiceNetMap, which can also be overridden.

commit_message:
Remove Redis VirtualIP from params and build it from Neutron::Port

The redis_vip should come from a Neutron Port as its cidr depends
on the Neutron Network configuration. This change adds 2 new files
and modifies 1 in the network/ports directory:

- noop.yaml - Passes through the ctlplane Controller IP (modified)
- ctlplane_vip.yaml - Creates a new VIP on the control plane
- vip.yaml - Creates a VIP on the named network (for isolated nets)

Also, changes to overcloud-without-mergepy.yaml create the
Redis Virtual IP. The standard resource registry was modified to
use noop.yaml for the new Redis VIP. The Puppet resource registry
was modified to use ctlplane_vip.yaml by default, but can be made
to use vip.yaml when network isolation is used by using an
environment file. vip.yaml will place the VIP according to the
ServiceNetMap, which can also be overridden.

We use this new VIP port definition to assign a VIP to Redis,
but follow-up patches will assign VIPs to the rest of the
services in a similar fashion.

Co-Authored-By: Dan Sneddon <dsneddon@redhat.com>

Change-Id: I2cb44ea7a057c4064d0e1999702623618ee3390c

commit_message:
test: add MatchType helper class as equivalent of mox.IsA

The mox test library had a helper method mox.IsA(SomeType) which
allowed unit tests to assert that a method call argument had a
particular type. The mock test library has a mock.ANY helper
which is often used, but nothing that allows a stricter checker
for a specific type. This patch introduces a MatchType class
which is similar to mock.ANY, but restricted to a single type.

So instead of using lots of mock.ANY parameters

   mock_some_method.assert_called_once_with(
                  "hello",
                  mock.ANY,
                  mock.ANY,
                  "world",
                  mock.ANY)

It becomes possible to be stricter

   mock_some_method.assert_called_once_with(
                  "hello",
                  MatchType(objects.Instance),
                  mock.ANY,
                  "world",
                  MatchType(objects.KeyPair))

Change-Id: I3a1ca33500ef8007b6c496e4e0917d7de07ac40a

commit_message:
Ensure that failing responses are logged

The boolean value of a failed response is False and so the way we
populate the log output does not work when the request failed.

When logging check that a response is not None rather than simply
checking it's boolean value.

Change-Id: I07fb46f156fdf8267fd3d4dc7c587cd604838d73
Closes-Bug: #1451625
(cherry picked from commit c7ec27a448d20201471a8f953e3b58b9ded589aa)

commit_message:
Stop using function deprecated in Python 3

Python 3 deprecated the logger.warn method in favor of warning.

 DeprecationWarning: The 'warn' method is deprecated, use 'warning'
 instead

Change-Id: Idbd4de3c7c631fb2c235701c9b300c37a90d9538
(cherry picked from commit c0046d7d0120ee18aab2f32ac6bdfca724d972ce)

commit_message:
Use random strings for test fixtures

Tests should use a random string so that we don't mistakenly use
the wrong string and not test what we think we're testing.

Change-Id: Ied0672db78a1e1cf2d390020cc5a49d0203683be
(cherry picked from commit 945e5195e8ba7aa53f6fd656aab81ead79d94449)

commit_message:
Typo in openstack client help

The openstack client output for the help of --os-user-id states
"longin" instead of "login".  The openstack client gets it's help
output from the keystoneclient.

Change-Id: I7c92a82cd60b2835d98101200cf641b46dd145b4
Closes-Bug: #1455673
(cherry picked from commit 7cf319e79002681ff7914a84bbc1e9af93d93e0f)

commit_message:
Drop use of 'oslo' namespace package

The Oslo libraries have moved all of their code out of the 'oslo'
namespace package into per-library packages. The namespace package was
retained during kilo for backwards compatibility, but will be removed by
the liberty-2 milestone. This change removes the use of the namespace
package, replacing it with the new package names.

The patches in the libraries will be put on hold until application
patches have landed, or L2, whichever comes first. At that point, new
versions of the libraries without namespace packages will be released as
a major version update.

Please merge this patch, or an equivalent, before L2 to avoid problems
with those library releases.

Blueprint: remove-namespace-packages
https://blueprints.launchpad.net/oslo-incubator/+spec/remove-namespace-packages

Change-Id: I387a7a1a817058a4daca313fe6df60612cb84864
(cherry picked from commit 3eb89ad7cc22b6afb5730ee2ee1c9e9b6502fe5c)

commit_message:
Adds horizon to pacemaker when puppet-pacemaker is enabled

Adds the horizon (httpd) service as pacemaker resource
Also adds a default for the horizon::django_session_engine [1]
which was previously unconfigured. Also adds a server-status.conf
for httpd/pacemaker [2]

[1] https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/dev/topics/http/sessions/#using-cached-sessions
[2] https://github.com/beekhof/osp-ha-deploy/blob/master/pcmk/horizon.scenario#L72

Change-Id: I320837dfecf3241355e8a3345d0ff271592da491

I am not sure that the bug is in heat. I faced with the same issues recently. It turns out that nova server don't become deleting(and stays in error) after no_valid_host_found because of some reasons.
I consulted with nova guys and they said that server should always become deleting(not error) when delete server api called and if it is not the bug can be potentially in nova.
Finally, it turns out that there were RAM space problems on master node. I guess you need more investigation but i am ready to change the opinion if there will be some explanation how it resolves the problem."}, {'account_id': 8289, 'date': '2015-06-11 13:11:09.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

(1 comment)

'deleting' is the task state, the server state won't be changed until the delete task done. It's possible that server in 'ERROR' but task in deleting, this is the reason of the problem."}, {'account_id': 7256, 'date': '2015-06-11 15:23:25.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1

I agree that I don't know that the bug is in Heat per-se. I think it may just be some odd behavior in Nova since I've seen deletes work fine even if servers are in ERROR. I don't think relying on this task status is reliable either since it can and does vary by operator and or available extensions."}, {'account_id': 8289, 'date': '2015-06-12 07:51:49.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

Randall Burt:
Thanks for reviewing, I think you can reproduce this problem easily(in my devstack to reproduce 100%) using the master codes. The state changing mechanism of nova is always this way, I think some changes of heat code increase the possibility of this problem. 
Another way to solve this is to delay the check-describing few seconds after deleting. 
Or other good suggestions?'}, {'account_id': 8289, 'date': '2015-06-12 09:22:33.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 2.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-06-12 10:46:11.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

commit_message:
Continue to check if nova task is in progress

Continue to check whether the nova server is deleted
completed if nova task is in progress. There is an attribute
'OS-EXT-STS: task_state' which showing task state in nova.

My preference is to submit changes in smaller patches but I'd like to know what your "logic" is behind this.'}, {'account_id': 15168, 'date': '2015-05-28 14:53:32.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

1st: Having different titles for commits would make git commit history cleaner. Typing git log and seeing 2/3 commits with the same title leaves the feeling that some mistakes was made.

I've just looked through them once again and noticed, that each commit works towards a specific part of documentation. Am I right? Then it actually makes some sense to split these changes into several patches. But could you please clarify in the commit message of each commit, that this commit improves specific part of docs?
Otherwise these commits look like an assorted bunch of changes, that were arbitrarily split into 3 commits, and can be easily combined into one.

On a side note -1 generally means, that "This patch needs further work before it can be merged" and that's what I thought. Not that I don't want these changes, I want to thank you for them! I just think, that these patches can be improved even more.'}, {'account_id': 9382, 'date': '2015-05-28 15:58:35.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 2.'}, {'account_id': 15168, 'date': '2015-05-28 16:01:54.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Code-Review+1'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-05-28 16:25:53.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Verified-1

correct the annotation of param

In the function trove.instance.service.py,
there is a function has four params,
the first three params's annotation is accurateÔºå
but the last param is incorrect,
so I correct it for others

It looks like lib/neutron_plugins/ovs_base sets up the external bridge properly in _neutron_ovs_base_configure_l3_agent, while that type of initialization is completely missing in lib/neutron_plugins/linuxbridge_agent.

So all tests that involve connectivity to a floating_ip will fail.'}, {'account_id': 13252, 'date': '2015-03-31 15:43:51.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

Ok, some progress here, with the localrc from http://paste.openstack.org/show/197715/ and manually setting the public ip as noted at the end of the paste between running ./stack.sh and run_tempest.sh, test_server_connectivity_pause_unpause is now working for me, still waiting for the results of a complete tempest run.

Seems like https://bugs.launchpad.net/devstack/+bug/1403625 is also involved here, as I think most people will also want to use the simpler default of vlan instead of vxlan.'}, {'account_id': 13252, 'date': '2015-03-31 15:56:09.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 2.'}, {'account_id': 13252, 'date': '2015-03-31 15:57:39.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

commit_message:
[WIP] Switch the default to Linuxbridge

This patch was created in response to a discussion regarding the
migration from nova-network to neutron [1]. It was argued that
the default of neutron using ovs would make the setup too complicated
for some operators, so we are looking here at the option of running
with linuxbridge as the default instead.

Note that this is still WIP, the intention of the patch is to find out
which things are breaking in the Jenkins tests and how to solve them.

[1] http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2015-March/060029.html

Co-Authored-By: Jens Rosenboom <j.rosenboom@x-ion.de>

Depends-On: If24bef2f8dd82f2cb257f0f311f5c1b742f77497

Change-Id: Ie7436d68b6921cd0db9eb28b55bc74583345c04f

cluster objects in heat stack.

commit_message:
Change future nova version number references based on new values

The nova server liberty version is changing from 2015.2 to 12.0.0 and
the 2016.1 'M' release will be 13.0.0 so update the deprecation warnings
in the docs and code using those versions.

Depends-On: I6a35fa0dda798fad93b804d00a46af80f08d475c

Change-Id: I716bac9a09d38de2b8a08ea88bfdb87a7fdeb661

commit_message:
Add puppet-zaqar Repository to Puppet Modules Project

This change adds the puppet-zaqar repository to the OpenStack Puppet
Modules project, which will contain the module necessary to configure
and manage OpenStack Zaqar with Puppet.

This change is related to a proposed governance change with ID of:

I660cc965dcc1aa8da6790c0db4ef657d58b487d3

Change-Id: Icb1e3e003f66f8f3c9bdd6b021ee497bcfc2f337

commit_message:
Add debian build test case

Weve had some regressions recently with the changes in the debian
element. Lets tests that we can build debian images.

Change-Id: I048e7a32ecb4088ec1b1e3b1efdf146187b093db

commit_message:
Fix namespace issue in generate_sample.sh

We just moved to using a hybrid approach that
uses the new oslo-config-generator for pulling out
library options to create the cinder.sample.conf file.
In that patch it was expected that we should use oslo_*
for the namespace.  That, however, is not how
oslo-config-generator works.

This patch switches to using oslo.* for the namespace to get
the library options pulled in.  This also fixes the fact that
we were putting multiple '[DEFAULT]' sections into the file.

Change-Id: Ie799d4d7e6deb2c486a93c5095fc3b766679fa95
Partial-bug:  1449235

commit_message:
Updated swift-ring-builder add command to new syntax

As per bug, the swift-ring-builder add command has updated syntax which
is simpler than the old syntax. This patch updated instances of this command
in the install guide to the new, simpler syntax.

Change-Id: I6892589e4209dab5ef34abae57f7e45b83939dc0
Closes-Bug: #1161928

commit_message:
Translate common-rst separately

To ease translation, translate common-rst in a separate po file.
Since we reuse the file in all RST guides, this needs special handling.

common-rst.pot is empty for now, we need the file so that the tools
work.

Change-Id: I9972e6222d4018b238da9b2b8f4e93e6ebc9e224
Co-Authored-By: KATO Tomoyuki <kato.tomoyuki@jp.fujitsu.com>

Move glance_store tests into the main package

We're moving glanceclient tests into the analogous directory, so we
should standardize and do the same in glance_store.

Change-Id: Icdcca1bd55be2d1ba8546bebf7ca1db72c183198

commit_message:
Moving hard-coded set of quotas to the config file

Now set of quotas is not hard-coded in tests and moved to the config
file. In addition, some unused variables were removed from tests in
test_quotas_nagative.py.

Closes-Bug: #1155390

Change-Id: I818e1bd92b05e33a5d8fe9091a31f48ae5aabeac

commit_message:
Adds hostutilsv2 to HyperV

Since RemoteFX works on Windows 2012 R2 it needs the "root\virtualization\v2"
WMI namespace.

This patch adds hostutilsv2 to Hyperv and the corresponding unit tests.

Partially implements blueprint: hyper-v-remotefx

Change-Id: I72e26df03b47d47c478635df39cb5baad6a3b596

commit_message:
Don't wait for VIF events if no creates needed

The wait for vif events from Neutron code is always invoked as it
stands.  This can cause an issue on reboots where the plug_vifs is
invoked on system init.  This is essentially part of the heal of the
system.

In this scenario, while nova does not create a VIF, it ends up waiting
for an event back from Neutron.  It never gets that event (because
Neutron has no action) and ends up timing out.

This change set rectifies this.  If there are no VIFs to create, then
the call to wait for Neutron never occurs.

Change-Id: If202bf6502a16eb12f1178f65ae01b42caed024f

commit_message:
Include unplug vifs and driver attach

This change set adds support for the Unplug VIFs operation.  It then
ties this operation in to the driver.

The driver was also updated such that the attach_interface method ties
to the plug_vifs and the detach_interface method ties to unplug_vifs
method.

Change-Id: I810d24d11d1357511d9a4af1e74d28008b15a2f0

commit_message:
Refactor scan_ports() and update_ancillary_ports() in OVS Neutron Agent

Used a helper method which contains the common code from scan_ports()
and update_ancillary_ports(). And also renamed the name of
update_ancillary_ports() method to scan_ancillary_ports() to have parity
between normal ports and ancillary ports.

Added unit tests for scan_ancillary_ports.

Co-Authored-By: Romil Gupta <romilg@hp.com>

Partial-Bug: #1329223

Change-Id: I8b3e00a9371d5a03cc8b4be24bf20eec10bef5df

commit_message:
Fix allocation pool in external.yaml

The file network/external.yaml has a typo in the last commit. It
should have been a get_param instead of a get_resource. This
change fixes that line in that file.

Change-Id: Ibc0db0510e9b5dae3c4669a620c642357906cbc2

[{'created': '2015-05-14 15:36:43.000000000', 'message': "Remove NO_SIGNAL from puppet role templates

commit_message:
Remove NO_SIGNAL from puppet role templates

Currently we use NO_SIGNAL on both the NetworkConfig and subsequent config
deploying the data associated with the role.  This means there is a risk that
should the NetworkConfig do anything interruptive (os-net-config can do
interface renaming based on discovery data for example) the role configuration
config could fail, and we'd never know until some later error occurs.

Additionally, we need to be sure that the heiradata deployed by each of the role
specicific configs is actually in-place before proceeding with any of the cluster
configuration - atm this works due to the inherent delays involved deploying to
bare-metal, but there's still a theoretical race if very fast deployment backends
(I'm thinking containers, e.g lxc backend to nova or something) were used instead.

Essentially, we should never be using NO_SIGNAL unless we want to ignore failure,
which AFAICT is not the case in this instance.

Change-Id: I0dbbcc87fb8df8e6bc4775c39fa616b0d0713464

@Henry: here is my workflow: I run all the tests in a py34 virtual environment, then see what errors happen, and how many times they happen. Then I try to fix  the most common ones.

I started with the iteritems/itervalues/... patches, because it is easy to grep all occurrences. Now, I'm starting to fix issues that are a bit harder to just grep. To make sure I caught all occurrences of this particular error, I'd need to write a (complex) static analyzer. I've ported a lot of OpenStack clients to python3, and I've rarely had to send a second patch to fix occurrences I had missed, so I think we should be ok."}, {'account_id': 6524, 'date': '2015-06-16 18:58:55.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: Workflow+1

commit_message:
Python3: do not change the size of a dict while iterating over it

This does not work in Python3, so we have to store the items first.

Change-Id: I7d8641f980fe62d2900559433d5060a6281a97f8
Blueprint: neutron-python3

Fix lint issues (doc, metadata, manifests)

Add puppet parameters lint (with puppet-lint-param-docs gem) and fix
missing documentations, this commit also fix manifest lint issues (due
to puppet-lint upgrade) and metadata.json file (SPDX license, and open
dependencies).

compatible with the puppet-glance 5.x series. Therefore we need to set

Change-Id: Iae0a8d3b54bf500f62bfc6fe1022c80e1ccb26f0

commit_message:
Set upper bound on puppet-openstacklib dependency

If we release puppet-openstacklib 6.0 we do not guarantee it is
compatible with the puppet-glance 5.x series. Therefore we need to set
an upper bound on the dependency in metadata.json.

Change-Id: Iae0a8d3b54bf500f62bfc6fe1022c80e1ccb26f0

regards to gate jobs.

commit_message:
Migrate postgresql backend to use openstacklib::db::postgresql

Let migrate to the new openstacklib::db::postgresql helper for
postgresql backend. This commit also unpin postgresql fixture
(openstacklib support now the latest version of postgre module).

Change-Id: I29ae9506cb638aa3e3925705bac945511c96ca8f
Implements: blueprint commmon-openstack-database-resource
(cherry picked from commit 7857c67e242712b7c7230d25c3f16438a48b414c)

commit_message:
Updates designate spec Domain properties

Update the designate resource plugin spec to make
email property as required one and ttl property
as optional one.

designate CLI error:
 CLI : designate domain-create --name test.org
 Error: domain-create: error: argument --email is required

blueprint heat-designate-resource

Change-Id: Icaeef5afdcd7bacd2e54cb076bb5433e76f9d478

commit_message:
Upgrade puppet-lint and fix metadata, parameter and style lint issues

This patch bump puppet-lint gem and add metadata and parameters checks.
Metadata lint issues (SPDX ID), missing parameters documentation and
syntaxe lint issues was also fixed in this patch

Doc for metadata syntax.
https://docs.puppetlabs.com/puppet/latest/reference/modules_publishing.html

Change-Id: Ia6bb3483b3ffdbeed60b58702a36e0c7b31ffb86
(cherry picked from commit 77be0932fc7d40a9bdf47c175c8ae5ffcc660f2f)

commit_message:
Fix the delete listener flow

Modified flows to receive appropriate arguments for flows to complete
Added task to delete listener from DB
Modified deletion tasks to remove listener from the DB rather than update to DELETED
Added tests for new task

Change-Id: I4e7c0310de13b5dab0f7a382b9c81a0b0c6e72ad
Closes-Bug: 1459001

commit_message:
Support host type specific block volume attachment

Add the platform and operating system type to the connector to allow a
Cinder driver to set host type specific configuration attributes when
attaching a Fibre-Channel volume.

Partial-Implements blueprint support-hosttype-on-attach

Change-Id: If37176758b4d7c16727415074ea2907589af6080

commit_message:
Allow control of hostname formatting

Currently, we use the heat default server names, which results in some
fairly unreadable hostnames due to the level of nesting in the templates.

e.g ov-sszdbj5rdne-0-bhseh65edxv6-Controller-zoqc6tlypbdp

Instead, we allow the user to specify a format string per role, defaulted
to a string which formats the name e.g <stackname>-controller-<index>

e.g overcloud-controller-0

Optionally additional hostname components (not replaced by heat) could be
added, such that deployment time customization of hostnames via firstboot
scripts (e.g cloud-init) may be possible.

Should anyone wish to maintain the old heat-generated names, they can pass
an empty string via these parameters, which heat will treat as if no "name"
property was provided to OS::Nova::Server.

Change-Id: I1730caa0c2256f970da22ab21fa3aa1549b3f90b

'}, {'created': '2015-06-16 21:53:17.000000000', 'message': "Add unit tests for Trove specs

Add simple unit tests to the Trove specs repo which ensure that
specifications submitted follow the template correctly and address
all the needed sections.

Update tox to run these unit tests automatically.

At the beginning of each release, test_titles.py will need to be updated
and 'current_release' modified to reflect the new release directory.  At
the same time, the new release directory will be created, the index.rst
file in doc/source ammended to include this directory, and any unmerged
specs moved there.  In this way, changes to the template will only
affect specs going forward and avoids having to modify any specs that
have merged in previous releases.

(It will also have the side effect of signalling the 'opening' of the

commit_message:
Add unit tests for Trove specs

Add simple unit tests to the Trove specs repo which ensure that
specifications submitted follow the template correctly and address
all the needed sections.

Update tox to run these unit tests automatically.

At the beginning of each release, test_titles.py will need to be updated
and 'current_release' modified to reflect the new release directory.  At
the same time, the new release directory will be created, the index.rst
file in doc/source ammended to include this directory, and any unmerged
specs moved there.  In this way, changes to the template will only
affect specs going forward and avoids having to modify any specs that
have merged in previous releases.

(It will also have the side effect of signalling the 'opening' of the
release to new specs.)

Change-Id: I8f1175bceed63d36d96b6c6c6b4188ef27d3102e

[{'created': '2015-06-15 16:26:57.000000000', 'message': 'Add $hostname.localdomain alias to /etc/hosts

We want to make sure to be able to resolve the default domain
suffix (.localdomain) appended when no domain option is passed by
the dhcp server.

Change-Id: I33111e91b502f57da442e5745de2217bd6d2d882
'}]
commit_message:
Add $hostname.localdomain alias to /etc/hosts

We want to make sure to be able to resolve the default domain
suffix (.localdomain) appended when no domain option is passed by
the dhcp server.

Change-Id: I33111e91b502f57da442e5745de2217bd6d2d882

commit_message:
Remove unused EnablePacemaker param from templates

Use of Pacemaker is governed by the resource registry since
change Ibefb80d0d8f98404133e4c31cf078d729b64dac3.

The param stayed longer in the template to prevent breakage of scripts
which could have passed it when launching stack-create, despite it being
ignored.

This change removes the param entirely.

Change-Id: I026ce391319a4306c4b81a15652e3cad470e5cb7
Depends-On: I775724b207c737043a2a418a3ec8ede2cbaa8fa0

commit_message:
Refactor TestRpcWorker and TestWorkerService

TestRpcWorker and TestWorkerService have a duplicate test_reset.
This patch introduces a base class from which tests for service
workers can inherit.

commit_message:
Shotgun: fixed password prompt when wrong ssh key

When shotgun tries to connect to a remote node with wrong
ssh key it falls into password dialog and prevents diagnostic
snapshot to be gathered. It is possible when, for example,
node is booted into bootstrap OS while nailgun thinks all
nodes are booted into target OS.

Change-Id: I7055ee1ac8d725c5f342f3255ef53018dd9d4022
Closes-Bug: #1466045

The Oslo libraries have moved all of their code out of the 'oslo'
namespace package into per-library packages. The namespace package was
retained during kilo for backwards compatibility, but will be removed by
the liberty-2 milestone. This change removes the use of the namespace
package, replacing it with the new package names.

The patches in the libraries will be put on hold until application
patches have landed, or L2, whichever comes first. At that point, new
versions of the libraries without namespace packages will be released as
a major version update.

Please merge this patch, or an equivalent, before L2 to avoid problems
with those library releases.

Blueprint: remove-namespace-packages

Change-Id: I0712fbf2bde2171775877e7748b3fdddc50186dc

commit_message:
Drop use of 'oslo' namespace package

The Oslo libraries have moved all of their code out of the 'oslo'
namespace package into per-library packages. The namespace package was
retained during kilo for backwards compatibility, but will be removed by
the liberty-2 milestone. This change removes the use of the namespace
package, replacing it with the new package names.

The patches in the libraries will be put on hold until application
patches have landed, or L2, whichever comes first. At that point, new
versions of the libraries without namespace packages will be released as
a major version update.

Please merge this patch, or an equivalent, before L2 to avoid problems
with those library releases.

Blueprint: remove-namespace-packages
https://blueprints.launchpad.net/oslo-incubator/+spec/remove-namespace-packages

Change-Id: I0712fbf2bde2171775877e7748b3fdddc50186dc

commit_message:
Set empty dhcp_domain for Neutron dhcp

When building the hostname list to be written into /etc/hosts we do
not append any domain part, Neutron should not append it either or
the guests' fqdn will not match any value found in /etc/hosts

Change-Id: Ice73e54b853506f228c98945c257740f72a68942

commit_message:
Added apt update tasks to everything using apt

This change adds a specific update task to all tasks that all the
apt ansible module. This change was done to ensure that the cache
is updated as expected when instructed to do so. The reason that
the cache update is being removed from the grouping is because
there is an upstream bug that is effecting the process by which
the apt cache is updated when there is a package list to process
within the same task. The work around to make this function as
expected is to move the update into its own task without a package
list.

Upstream Ansible bug:
  - https://github.com/ansible/ansible-modules-core/issues/1497

Change-Id: Ic06d89a76d772c12888b4bc4bbf147be58b0c150
Related-Bug: 1464771
(cherry picked from commit 59381b51ffb83bd67e13d5f04ff731f1b70a67bf)

commit_message:
Release Notes 6.1 -- Known&Resolved Issues (Partner)

This commit focuses at VMware issues only.
Note, that NSX issues were removed from the list
with a note about plugin.

Change-Id: I9663c54386ca3e00ae1f3c87f2c8d72c24edd6bb

commit_message:
Refactor verify_list tests

Rework the verify_list testing to put more of the guts into the
implementation instead of having a lot of common things passed in
arguments.

Additionally, this adds an explicit pagination argument in calls to
_list, which is one of the steps we need to take in properly completing
the pagination calls per bug #1465756.

Partial-Bug: 1465756

Change-Id: If75813d28e915f7a62c23a0059afada7fb3e575f

commit_message:
Add _at suffix to created/updated Server attrs

Other resources use an _at suffix for timestamp related things, and
Server had `created` and `updated` without those suffixes. Those kinds
of names would more commonly be associated with boolean options.

Change-Id: I0aeaf9176c5ecb41cd92f261cdabc411900d7b1e
Closes-Bug: 1435880

commit_message:
Fix Cisco UCS slow tests

This patch sets the cisco_ucs.action_interval configuration option in the
tests to 0, so that we don't spend time sleeping when testing the driver.

Closes-Bug: #1465239
Change-Id: Ic5780d196ce58bc5f8628e6998f2b2554d4a869a

commit_message:
Fixes a typo 'use_strict' -> 'use strict'

Apparently strict mode is not enabled in toast widgets, due to a
'use_strict' typo, that must have crept in during jscs cleanup
This commit fixes the typo.

Closes-Bug: #1466003
Change-Id: I4cf30b8343bba6bbe7932e3927c6cbc8a81dc0df

commit_message:
make SchedulerV3PassthroughTestCase use NoDBTest

SchedulerV3PassthroughTestCase only contains mocks so
no need to make it DB test cases, otherwise it will be
the slowest one if only unit.scheduler is tested.

I kind of want to do another blueprint that will propose replacing the current sqlalchemy-migrate fixed migration files with Alembic migrations, and then organize the Alembic migrations themselves into branches (juno, kilo, liberty) and additionally "expand" / "contract" branches as well.   I will then propose that the functionality here be integrated with the Alembic system, such that the automation here is used to generate new Alembic files.  This will fix the limitation that many kinds of migrations, such as column type changes, are not allowed, because they cannot be automated.   For the use case of third-party additions, these deployers can in fact write their own alembic migration scripts in branches that they declare locally, so that their migrations will also be versioned and merged against what is in the release itself.

I think it's important to A. always be able to accommodate *any* kind of migration, not just those that can be fully automated and B. ensure that a database schema is always in a known and documented state, rather than any arbitrary state that the automation system here has to attempt to correct for.   Alembic's new featureset which was not released until recently makes it possible for a single database to report on any number of tags / branches that it satisfies.'}, {'account_id': 100, 'date': '2015-04-16 16:42:40.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 13:

This blueprint/feature has been very frustrating for me.

It took a long time to get people to review the original blueprint and to review the implementation.

It died with reviews saying they don't understand it and are just trusting me. This is the last place I want to be in. I don't want to be the only person that understands something. It doesn't do Nova any favors and I don't want to be the only person who is willing to work on any particular code. I'm surprised the blueprint ever got approved after some of the comments on the implementation.

I've moved to another group recently and I'm only tangentially involved in Nova now. So I'm going to abandon this blueprint/feature.

It's hard me to say what you should do since I won't be involved in the future, but please take the time to at least understand the original problems I was trying to solve. I'd hate to see a solution that doesn't really solve the problems in a way that the majority of people can actually use."}, {'account_id': 100, 'date': '2015-04-16 16:42:46.000000000', 'content': 'Abandoned'}, {'account_id': 11816, 'date': '2015-04-16 17:19:36.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 13:

No matter what happens, a lot of good has already come from this effort, in terms of setting up the flow of "expand" and "contract" which I hope to continue, as well as the great improvements you've made to the Alembic project itself as a result, and I do want to continue to evaluate if there is a place for automated on-the-fly migrations from an undefined state to a defined one to take place; I understand that vendors do things like add and remove their own indexes and things like that (already got bit by trying to add an index to a table this week).   I think maybe if the "expand" and "contract" workflows that aren't necessarily hand-written but are visible as static code that's committed to the source might help to demystify the system for others; this is after all the current design philosophy of Alembic.

I apologize that I didn't spend more time with the original spec; my main reaction to it at the time was just to get Alembic to be the tool of record for it, so I went off and tried to repair all the issues reported against Alembic.

We have moved further along no matter what migration approach is ultimately delivered for Nova and others.'}, {'account_id': 1849, 'date': '2015-05-20 21:51:06.000000000', 'content': 'Restored'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-05-20 21:53:57.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 13:

Obviously, for those reading my open thinking on the mailing list, I'm continuing to try to understand the full impact of exactly how data migrations will work within oslo.versionedobjects and what kind of database code that creates within models and database access layers.

But at the same time, I'm still not accepting that there are any real downsides to allowing the expand/contract workflow to still generate its calculations into fixed, version controlled migration files rather than going with a fully dynamic approach, and I am not accepting that the advantages of fixed migration files are worth abandoning, especially considering that we'd like this feature to apply very well to other projects besides Nova.    I get a sense that because SQLAlchemy-Migrate is so bad, that's what people are assuming is the case with fixed-file schema migration systems in general; having to generate specific numbers, having to do "migration compaction", "no more sqlalchemy-migrate migrations would need to be [manually] written", these are all things that aren't needed anymore.
 
The blueprint makes an effort at addressing this alternative, but the arguments it makes against it are obsolete or otherwise don't make much sense to me.

The first argument stated is: "This limits the schema changes that can be safely executed online to that of the lowest common denominator of databases supported by Nova." I've read this sentence many times and I really don't know what it's talking about.   The directives we are invoking here in this implementation are already Alembic migration directives; they are already database agnostic.  Whether they are invoked on the fly or rendered into a migration script first, then invoked, makes no difference at all.  If the argument is that on some backends, online schema generations might impact objects that Nova doesn't otherwise know about and therefore wouldn't be present in a fixed-file migartion, I don't really know what that's referring to either.  It's not like Nova has explicit use of special objects such as database sequences or anything like that, it already can only use the "lowest common denominator" of explicit features in any case, except those features for which SQLAlchemy dialects are providing backend-specific implementations (like autoincrement).   If someone could show me an example of what wouldn't work on a previously unknown database backend with a fixed migration script that *does* work with the online approach here, that would help me to understand what this is referring to.   Having a fixed, version-controlled migration script IMO makes it *easier* to support odd features of unusual database backends, because the scripts can be altered to support those special operations on a case-by-case, conditional basis until Alembic can be upgraded to accommodate those features automatically (and therefore by the fully "online" engine as well, which relies upon Alembic to do the actual database interaction).

The second argument is, "This would also require changes to sqlalchemy-migrate to be able to manage separate streams of migrations." This is also a non-issue, because Alembic supports separate streams of migrations fully, and the expand/contract workflow would be fully available, such that individual per-release expand/migrate/contract branches could be grouped into per-release directories (or whatever).  The feature as described at http://alembic.readthedocs.org/en/latest/branches.html was requested by many users, but as I implemented this some months ago, being able to support this very blueprint was one of my goals.  I was disappointed that even though I commented on the blueprint on Nov 21 that this feature was now available, the blueprint was not updated to include this new information and was merged over a month later still containing obsolete information assuming the use of SQLAlchemy-Migrate and the unavailability of this feature.
 
Let's consider the *advantages* of using fixed, version-controlled migration files:   

1. While Nova is obviously never going to have data migrations in their migration streams, having an explicit migration stream with fixed states will allow *other* projects which use the expand/contract model to have this as an option that can be used when appropriate - and I am trying to make this a feature that will work well for other projects and allow enough flexibility for scenarios that might not be exactly the same as those of Nova.   For the case especially where we are dealing with read-only data, the document at http://docs.openstack.org/developer/nova/devref/upgrade.html states "For records that are not updated, you need to run a background process to convert those records into the newer format." - Really?  If you just allow regular in-migration-stream data migrations to take place within the "expand" phase, now you don't have to write a background process for fixed data migrations; after "expand" proceeds, now your fixed data is in both versions of the model.  There is no longer a need for a "background process", I am not sure if there is an existing framework for these processes to be built but this still seems much more complicated than writing a single INSERT statement in a script.    IMO, having data migrations available as an option, at least for other projects, is a profound advantage to building the system such that the migration stream is represented as a series of discrete, fixed states.

2. The migrations are written out explicitly, and committed to source, which exist then as a fixed record of how the migrations will proceed, which is IMO more useful than just the "--dryrun" or "--as-sql" flag that only gives you an ad-hoc SQL dump of what will happen (that option of course still remains as well since this is just an Alembic feature).   There's no longer a strong need for operators to run the "expand" phase with "--as-sql" and carefully check that nothing surprising happens; when the migration stream is fixed and explicit, we ensure there are no surprises before we ever release the software.  Operators can of course still run a dry run.

3. The caveat in the spec which states "Deployers that have made local schema changes (extra indexes, columns, tables, etc) will need to update the model to ensure those additions aren't dropped during the contract phase." - that impact goes away if we use fixed migration files; in fact even with the fully "online" approach here, there are ways that the system could limit itself to just a known universe of symbols and not impact additional structures that a deployer may be maintaining separately.

If Nova devs could respond to these points, that would help to assuage my concerns that the move to abandon migration files totally isn't being made predjudicially due to SQLAlchemy-Migrate's lack of features.   As I stated in my email thread, I didn't engage enough with the original blueprint, and I would like to ensure that the alternative approaches here as they exist today, not as they existed eleven months ago, have been fully considered before moving forward with this approach.

Thanks for reading!'}, {'account_id': 100, 'date': '2015-05-22 17:31:48.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 15.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-05-22 18:32:25.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 15: Verified+1
